fields.name: ZALORA
fields.description: ZALORA is one of four e-marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other three are Namshi (The Gulf Region), LaModa (Russia & the former CIS) and THE ICONIC in Australia and New Zealand. All Global Fashion Groups e-marketplaces sell top international and local fashion brands in fashion and beauty. ZALORA covers 6 markets in South East Asia. A variety of operating models are offered on the platform.
fields.customer_demographics: Fashion forward and fashion conscious male and female customers aged 20-40. Specific insights will vary across markets according to what retail channels already exist, the brands currently available, and general income levels.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
A range of marketing communication tools and services are available, including: on-site marketing banners, mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, Zalora's in-house online magazine, TV advertising, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

Pricing is available on request from the Global Fashion Group team.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell on Zalora, brands will require a good level of international brand awareness, technical capability to integrate with the platform, and proven overseas fulfilment capability.

fields.name: Newegg Inc
fields.description: Newegg is the #1 online marketplace for everything tech in the U.S. From consumer electronics to home automation to car electronics, you can sell your products to over 30 million interested customers. Streamline your business by leveraging 'Shipped by Newegg' fulfilment solutions--you can put consignment stock in the US, which they will pick, pack, and dispatch for you. Capitalise on the low commission fees and drive effective marketing and merchandising campaigns by coordinating with a dedicated category and merchandising team.
fields.customer_demographics:
63% Male, 37% Female customers
51% earn $60K+, 22% earn $100K+
2.3M+ social fans across 9 platforms
3M+ customer product reviews
fields.marketing_merchandising: Newegg offers exposure opportunities on a variety of marketing and merchandising vehicles, such as home page and category page exposure, as well as segmented email blasts and more. A+ Content optimisation (an enhanced product listing) is available for $60 USD per SKU. All Sellers have a Dedicated Category Manager and Merchandiser.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Required within 72 hours of receiving an order and subject to Newegg minimum performance. Or use Shipped by Newegg and let them take care of order fulfilment and logistics.
fields.ukti_terms: Commission reduced from 12% to 11% (and down to 10% for those selling over $100k/month)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Newegg provides a great opportunity to trade in the USA with fewer barriers. One key differentiator is that they act as the ‘merchant of record’, therefore you will have no liability regarding US sales tax. Don't forget to use American English where appropriate in your product listings.

fields.name: Otto
fields.description: From its early beginnings as a catalogue business, Otto has now expanded to include an e-marketplace as well. The success of the business is based on best-in-class logistics and customer support, with specific expertise in consumer electronics and home furnishing.
fields.customer_demographics: 9 million active customers, women aged 25-55, 62% of whom are married women with above average income. The Otto Group reaches  45% of all German households in urban, semi-urban and rural locations via its catalogue and e-markeplace businesses.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
A range of advertising and communications services are available, including special on-site advertising formats (banners), social media, a customer newsletter and branded online areas.

Extra fees may apply depending on the services required, and are negotiated direct between the merchant and Otto.
fields.ukti_terms: The 10,000 Euro registration fee that normally applies is waived for UK merchants that Otto agrees terms with.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers will require a minimum of 100 Stock Keeping Units (SKUs), experience with XML files for technical integration, previous e-marketplace experience, and will also need to translate their content into German. These criteria are non-negotiable.

fields.name: Xiu
fields.description:
Xiu.com is a Chinese cross-border e-retailer with 12 million registered users. Founded in March 2008, Xiu.com sells mid-to-high range and luxury products including Apparel (30%), Shoes (20%), Bags (20%), Beauty (10%), Accessories
(10%), Jewellery and Watches (8%), and Home (2%).
This represents low-cost entry to the Chinese market, offering a drop ship model for selected UK partner brands.
fields.customer_demographics: Customer age group: 25-45, 55% female customers, 45% male customers. 70% of Xiu's customers live in 1st and 2nd tier cities; 30% of the customers are from 3rd and 4th tier cities.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Developing brand awareness is of fundamental importance in China. Xiu.com are willing to handle your marketing budget if you will commit to them exclusively and agree not to sell on other platforms. Brands are advised to reinvest 30% of turnover in their marketing. Without exclusivity, Xiu.com will offer basic promotion on the site for free .
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Deliver direct to the Consumer in China
fields.commission_notes: There is no commission as Brands agree a price xiu.com  team
fields.ukti_terms: This is a drop ship model with zero on-boarding fees. Individually negotiated prices with brands.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Building brand awareness in China across multiple consumer touchpoints both online and offline, in the UK and China, is imperative to make a success of Chinese market entry.

fields.name: Tmall Global
fields.description:
Launched in February 2014, Tmall Global (TMG) is a cross-border e-commerce marketplace in China. This is a popular platform for Chinese consumers within the Alibaba network and gives access to 434 million users across the Alibaba network.

Tmall Global operate a selective application process prior to brands launching their store.
This is a multi-product platform with key categories of Apparel, Handbags, Cosmetics, Homeware, Baby Formula and Women's Shoes.

This is a multi-quality e-marketplace, including Luxury, Premium and Economy.
fields.customer_demographics: All demographics shop at Tmall
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brands need to engage the services of a third party to run the core functions of the store. These functions include: translations, imagery, optimised descriptions, customer service, return handling. Costs for these services are by negotiation. It is essential for brands to raise awareness in China and a marketing budget must be set aside to encourage brand engagement. Marketing on Tmall takes many forms often driven by price promotions.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Logistics provided by Third Party Partner
fields.ukti_terms: None yet agreed.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: This can be carried out by the TP
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: This can be carried out by the TP
fields.registration_fees_notes: These fees are taken care of by the TP
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Trademark registration prior to entering the Chinese market is considered best practice. Payment terms: 1-14 days (depends on when the brand reaches the minimum balance transfer threshold). •	Deposit: 50.000 RMB - 100.000 RMB (depending on the type of store: flagship store, multi brand marketplace, etc.).•	Membership fee: 30.000 RMB - 60.000 RMB (depending on category)

fields.name: VIP Shop
fields.description:
Launched in Sep 2014, VIP Global is an independent channel on VIP.com selling only foreign brands. The overall VIP.com (NYSE: VIPS) business is ranked 3rd in terms of turnover which reached 6.2 billion USD for 2015. VIP has 19.7 million daily unique visitors and 200 million registered users.
This is a multi-product platform with key categories of Apparel, Home, Handbags, Shoes, Cosmetics & Beauty, Mother & Baby products, Toys  and Food & Drink.
VIP has an office in London which can liaise with UK companies on a day to day basis, during UK business hours.

VIP will buy the products or operate with consignment which is a matter of individual commercial negotiations between brands and the VIP buying teams.
fields.customer_demographics: 75% of registered users are females aged 18 - 45 yrs. 80% of all sales on VIP are carried out on mobiles.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Pricing is set by agreement between VIP and partner brands. VIP sells both in season and off season products.  Brands can leverage the VIP visitors and pay for some marketing.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Bulk delivery to nominated carrier with marketplace fulfilling to customer
fields.ukti_terms: This is either a wholesale model or a consignment model (fashion) with zero onboarding fees. Prices are individually negotiated with brands.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: VIP will carry out the translation
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: VIP will carry out the translation
fields.dit_advisor_tip: The greater the brand recognition in China, the greater will be the interest from the VIP team. Brands should consider registering their trademarks prior to expanding into China.

fields.name: 1688.com
fields.description: 1688.com is a sister website of Alibaba.com. It is China's leading online business to business (B2B) marketplace enabling UK businesses to sell to millions of buyers across China. 1688.com has 120 million users and 10 million companies have their products listed on this site. There are 49 main categories of goods. Price sensitive buyers are particularly interested in UK food, beverage and cosmetics.
fields.customer_demographics: This is a B2B site with popular UK categories (sub-categories) of Beauty & Personal Care (shampoo), Mother and Baby (infant milk), Food and Beverage (spices and wine), and Kitchen Appliances (water purifiers). Buyers are price sensitive, and brands will need to consider competitors on the platform and their pricing structure.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brands need to engage the services of an authorised trusted party (TP) to help run the store and offer guidance and feedback on pricing. Prices for this TP service are by negotiation with the TP. Brand awareness in China amongst target consumers is essential for success in China. Good store management and product imagery combined with a robust marketing budget will be more likely to drive increased sales.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Bulk goods delivered into China by seller
fields.ukti_terms: This is a wholesale model and no special terms are available.
fields.local_bank_account_needed_notes: This can belong to local importer
fields.local_incorporation_needed_notes: The can be the brands local importer
fields.translation_application_process_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.dit_advisor_tip: This is a B2B platform for Chinese companies. It is therefore necessary for UK businesses to work with a local partner or set up their own legal entity. Goods will need to comply with all local health and certification procedures which can be undertaken by specialist suppliers or a nominated partner.

fields.name: Alibaba Direct
fields.description: Alibaba Group is building a direct purchase team, in an effort to bring more global brands onto the Tmall Global platform. This team is interested in brands with a high level of awareness and demand in China, but which are not otherwise available through the Alibaba platforms. Alibaba direct purchase team will buy wholesale either with forward orders or from available stock. This Alibaba-run shop is called Jinkou, and it listed on Tmall Global in March 2016.
fields.customer_demographics: All demographics shop on Tmall Global where the Jinkou store is hosted.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Established recognition is a prerequisite condition. The Direct Buy Team will work with the brand to leverage its existing marketing resources in its home country, and it will produce localised marketing information which will then be promoted through Alibaba's own marketing channels.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK seller deliver to UK hub and Alibaba take care of the rest
fields.ukti_terms: This is wholesale model with zero onboarding fees. Prices are individually negotiated with brands.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Register your trademark for China first. Building brand awareness amongst Chinese consumers should be central to any Chinese strategy.

fields.name: Shangpin
fields.description: Shangpin was established in 2010 as one of the leading luxury and fashion online platforms in China, and offers over 1400 brands. It provides access to China’s mid-to-high end fashion consumers, extending into the luxury market. Shangpin is not only an online platform, more of a premium online fashion retailer. In 2014, as the exclusive online partner of Arcadia Group in China, Shangpin introduced TOPSHOP/TOPMAN into the country. The platform has 32 million registered users, and offers a simple drop ship model for UK brands. Shangpin has 10 photographic teams for imagery, and works with a group of celebrities and Key Opinion Leaders (KOLs), as well as running general marketing and promotions for the brands. This offers low-cost entry for selected brands.
fields.customer_demographics: Customers demographics are 60% women and 40% men. The customer base is comprised of fashion-conscious buyers from 16 years and up. The average basket size is $200, and Shangpin has repeat purchase rates of 80%.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Shangpin has 10 photographic teams for imagery, and they work with a group of celebrities and Key Opinion Leaders (KOLs), as well as running general marketing and promotions for brands. Alongside this marketing offered by Shangpin, brands should set aside about 20% of projected annual turnover for their own additional marketing budget.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK Sellers deliver directly to Chinese consumers home address
fields.commission_notes: This is a drop ship model where prices are pre-agreed
fields.ukti_terms: This is a drop ship model with zero onboarding fees. Prices are individually negotiated between Shangpin and the brand.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Brands should register their trademarks prior to launching into the Chinese market. To succeed in China, promotion and brand awareness is crucial, and must therefore be budgeted. The greater the brand awareness in China, the more likely that Shangpin will work with a brand.

fields.name: JD Worldwide
fields.description: JD Worldwide has 35% of China's B2C e-commerce market and is a cross-border e-commerce site offering products from overseas. It has 188 million annual active customers (those who have shopped at least once in the previous 12 months). They have two business models, one is the seller's own store, where a brand will have their own shop and sell directly to consumers, and the other model involves wholesale purchases by JD from the brands.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week; also through App
fields.customer_demographics: Demographic of 188 million JD registered users: 68% male, 32% female. 80% of shoppers are aged 18-45, and 65% have attained university degrees.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brands need to engage the services of a third party to run the core functions of the store. Translations, imagery, optimised descriptions, customer service and return handling. Costs for these services are by negotiation. It is essential for brands to raise awareness in China, and a marketing budget must be set aside to encourage greater brand engagement.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Logistics provided by sellers third party partner
fields.ukti_terms: $1000 annual fee will be waived for UK companies for the first year
fields.translation_product_content_notes: To Be Provided by Local Partner
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: To Be Provided by Local Partner
fields.deposit_notes: Deposit is $10,000-$15,000 depends on certain metrics
fields.dit_advisor_tip: JD.com can integrate with a WeChat store which can offer a powerful online combination for UK brands.

fields.name: Allegro
fields.description: Allegro is one of the most popular online shopping destinations in Poland. Over 18 million visitors shop the site monthly, contributing to the sale of over 850,000 items on the platform every day. The most notable product categories include Fashion, Electronics, Home & Garden and Kids & Baby. Allegro have developed a special channel called Brand Zone, which is available to brand owners and official distribution partners across all product categories.
fields.seller_support_hours: Email 24 hours / 7 days a week, Phone 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM CET
fields.customer_demographics:
47% Male, 53% Female
Age: 26% - 15-24 years old, 34% - 25-34 years old, 34% - 35-49 years old.
City population 39% - Cities with up to 200k residents.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Allegro ads system, promotional options: featuring, highlighting, bolding, promotion on product category page, daily deals, brand zone, Ad placements: showcase on main page, landing pages, etc.
fields.ukti_terms: Special marketing package worth GB £1k
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell successfully on Allegro, you will need to be able to offer Polish customer service. To translate your product listings accurately, make sure you use a native speaker, and avoid machine translation.

fields.name: Spartoo
fields.description: Spartoo.co.uk is an e-commerce website specialising in shoes and clothing. Based in Grenoble, France, it was created in 2009 as part of the company Spartoo.com. Spartoo offers first line customer service in 12 different languages and operates in 30 European countries. They work with sellers via a standard marketplace dropship model, allowing them to sell into all the countries where they have presence.
fields.customer_demographics: Core Demographic: Women, 30 to 40
fields.marketing_merchandising: No merchandising, 12 million spent on online marketing per year. As with all marketplaces, you can make your products more visible by writing good product titles, making sure product descriptions are detailed, and adding multiple high-quality images to show items from several angles and zoom in for detail.
fields.ukti_terms: Spartoo will waive their Monthly Account Fee (£30) for three months.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Spartoo will only work with sellers who can offer a minimum of 250 SKUs. Although a relatively small player in the UK, Spartoo are a household name in France and across much of Europe. Spartoo offers a great one-stop solution to access Europe’s huge online fashion market.

fields.name: FlipKart
fields.description: Flipkart is India's largest e-commerce marketplace, with over 65% market share in major categories. Key product categories include Electronics, Fashion, Kids & Baby, Homeware, and Sports & Fitness. UK brands must partner with an Indian aggregator to sell on the platform (Flipkart can make the introduction). This aggregator acts as the registered seller and manages the seller's operations in India, including listings, managing inventory, returns, customer service, and shipping and customs clearance.
fields.customer_demographics: Flipkart caters to Tier 1, 2 and 3 cities. The majority of online shoppers are under 35.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Flipkart will support merchandising for brands who meet product selection and expected pricing benchmarks. They have various channels to promote brands directly on the platform and via affiliates. They also offer special merchandising packages on a paid basis.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Seller to Aggregator, Aggregator to Customer
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.shipping_tracking_required_notes: Flipkart's aggregator will collect the items from the seller's location and handle delivery.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Indian consumers are very price-conscious and having the right pricing strategy can be the difference between success and failure in India. The costs to sell are significant: when you factor in customs duties, Flipkart's commission, the aggregator's margin, and local VAT, it can add up to between 25% and 80% of your margin.

fields.name: Trade Me
fields.description: Trade Me is New Zealand's most popular website and largest digital platform - in fact, 75% of all domestic web traffic in New Zealand goes to Trade Me. They offer a strong product and brand demand, in the opposite season to the Northern hemisphere, and sell everything from apparel to sports gear and car parts. Top-selling categories include Fashion, Computers/ Electronics, Toys & Hobbies, Home & Living, Baby, Sports, Health & Beauty and Jewellery. Brands and retailers are invited to join the platform based on likelihood of success in market and category demand.
fields.customer_demographics: 85% of the population of New Zealand hold an account with TradeMe so the platform reaches a very broad demographic spread.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
TradeMe offers the following marketing solutions for brands with good commercial opportunity:

1. Display advertising across site

2. Solus email marketing

3. Newsletter inclusion (1.6 million subscribers)

4. Social media push (100k Facebook, 17k Twitter) They may also consider external marketing for the right brand.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: Integrators include: Channel Advisor, Black Pepper
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Trade Me can make recommendations on logistics partners
fields.ukti_terms: 15% reduction in commission from 9.85% gross (including payment fees) to 8.37%
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Trade Me wants to work with sellers with strong e-commerce experience - as a general guideline, you should have a £1million/year online turnover. Marketplace experience (e.g. on eBay or Amazon) is also preferable.

fields.name: Cdiscount
fields.description: With 7.7 million active users (as of Q2 2016) and 11 million unique visitors to the site every month, Cdiscount is an essential marketplace in France. It offers an extensive range of products in over 40 different categories, such as apparel, shoes & accessories, consumer electronics, jewellery, entertainment, sports equipment, games & toys, and food & drink. In addition, Cdiscount operate their own fulfillment service, making this marketplace a great option for any retailer looking to expand their business in the French market. They offer best-in-class delivery options, with a network of 18,500 pickup points.
fields.seller_support_hours: Online/Email: 24 hours, 7 days a week, Phone: 8:30 AM - 9:00 PM (GMT +1)
fields.customer_demographics: Broad demographics due to wide product selection.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Cdiscount offers various communication tools to increase sellers' visibility on the marketplace. Their 'Pole Position Program' can help sellers to improve visbility, increase traffic, boost sales, strengthen customer loyalty and receive more product reviews.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Seller responsible for shipping, unless using C Logistique, which is available at extra cost
fields.ukti_terms: Monthly account fee (€39) waived for 3 months
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Cdiscount has been around since 1998 and is a household name among French consumers. They are particularly well known for electronics and tech products, and are popular with tech-savvy shoppers looking for good prices.

fields.name: Amazon China
fields.description: Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas.
fields.customer_demographics: Men and women of all ages
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost:

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

fields.name: Amazon Spain
fields.description: Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas.
fields.customer_demographics: Men and women of all ages
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost:

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
By using Amazon's easy to use functionality, sellers can use their UK account to list products in Spain and three other European countries (France, Germany & Italy).

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
Sellers will need to set up a US$ bank account to receive payment from Amazon USA. This can be arranged via a UK High Street Bank or through a payment services company such as WorldPay.

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
Sellers will need to use professional services (legal, accounting and financial) to trade on Amazon Japan, for example Jumbo and Windows.

Sellers must arrange to receive Japanese Yen with a third party provider. They must either arrange for them to transfer the money into sterling, or open a bank account in Japanese Yen for the provider to send funds to.

fields.dit_advisor_tip:
Sellers should set up a currency account in Canadian $ in order to accept payment from Amazon Canada.

Sellers can also sell on amazon.ca to sell on amazon.com and amazon.mx without paying an extra membership fee.

fields.name: Etsy
fields.description: Etsy is a global marketplace connecting buyers and sellers in almost every country in the world, both online and offline, to make, sell and buy unique goods. Etsy offers support to emerging and established creative companies. They have 26 million buyers and 1.70 million registered sellers, worldwide. The heart of Etsy is their global community of sellers. There are numerous channels of support for sellers.
fields.customer_support_hours: Online help centre accessible all the time
fields.seller_support_hours: Online help centre accessible all the time
fields.customer_demographics: People of all ages across the globe visit the site, looking for new ideas and gifts
fields.marketing_merchandising: Etsy believe advertisements should help sellers grow their businesses and contribute to the overall member experience. Etsy offer multiple advertising channels to sellers to promote their listings. Their Advertising Policy explains sellers' rights and responsibilities when using Etsy’s advertising services.
fields.ukti_terms: 20 free listings for new sellers who come through DIT.
fields.fee_per_listing_notes: $0.20 ( about 15 pence depending on exchange rate)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Most popular products are: 1) Clothing & Accessories 2) Jewellery 3) Craft Supplies & Tools 4) Weddings 5) Entertainment 6) Home & Living 7) Kids & Baby 8) Vintage.

fields.name: Westwing
fields.description:
Westwing is a shoppable online magazine and an e-marketplace. It provides the latest reviews and content about products, whilst enabling consumers to buy them from the platform.
Westwing run five online marketing campaigns per day in each country in which they operate. Every campaign lasts around four to six days.
fields.customer_demographics: 95% of Westwing's customer base is female and aged 25-60 years of age. Over 50% have a monthly income of 3,000 Euros. In Germany, the average Westwing consumer spends over 1,700 Euros on interior furnishings each year, which is twice the German national average. Across all markets where Westwing operates its customers are passionate about decorations and home furnishings, avidly follow social media and digital platfoms such as Pinterest, Instagram and Snapchat
fields.marketing_merchandising: Specific marketing terms can be agreed between the seller and e-marketplace. This normally takes the form of an additional discount on the seller list price to pay for marketing activities that Westwing manages on its own channels and via other partners. Alternatively sellers can invest their own marketing budgets to support sell-through of products on the platform. Westwing is active on multiple social media channels (Facebook, YouTube, Instagram, Snapchat), and partners with local bloggers in each market to promote listed products to its' audiences.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Westwing operates a wholesale model in a wide range of markets, with a particular focus on major European countries. UK sellers will be able to deliver to a specified Westwing distribution centre in each of the European countries covered by the platform, but will need to use their own local distributors if selling to customers in Russia or Brazil.

fields.name: eBay
fields.description: eBay connect sellers to 164 million buyers worldwide, including 22 million active users in the UK.  80% of products sold on the platform are new, and 86% sold at fixed price rather than auction. 58% of eBay's sales are international / cross border trade.
fields.customer_demographics: All demographics are eBay customers - a reflection of the wide range of items listed.
fields.marketing_merchandising: EBay offers a suite of tools including eBay Shops (branded stores or micro-sites), Seller Hub and Promote Your Listings to help you drive traffic and sales.
fields.ukti_terms: eBay will waive the Shop Subscription Fee for an initial trial period of six months when subscribing to the eBay Shop Anchor level on www.eBay.co.uk (value £217.38 per month).
fields.fee_per_listing_notes: eBay offers a choice of options. Listing fees are shown on the web site, and charged on sale.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: The eBay Global Shipping Programme (GSP) makes international postage as simple as selling to someone in the UK.  All you need to do is post the item to a UK Shipping Centre, and eBay will take care of customs clearance, tracking and all the rest. You don’t have to pay anything extra - just the cost of posting the item to the UK Shipping Centre.

fields.name: Ctrip
fields.description: Founded in 1999 and listed on Nasdaq in 2003, Ctrip is the largest online provider of travel services in China including accommodation reservation, transportation, ticketing, package tours and corporate travel management. Ctrip has had more than 1 billion downloads of its mobile application and has 250 million registered users. Ctrip Global Shopping, is a pioneering O2O (offline to online) shopping programme launched in 2014. Ctrip have developed an online shopping e-marketplace directed at their 250 million members, offering a wide variety of international products, services and gift cards. Ctrip is looking to build relationships with retailers who are looking to attract Chinese overseas travellers.
fields.customer_demographics: 61.8% Women, 38.2% Men. 88% between the ages of 20-40 years. International travellers and predominantly high net worth individuals.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Ctrip employs a wide variety of marketing initiatives to promote products. These include product listing destination recommendations, SMS/Electronic Direct Mail promotions, Geo-Location push messaging, banner advertising and WeChat promotions.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK sellers to deliver direct to the consumer, eith local hotel, airport or overseas address
fields.ukti_terms: Special reduced commission rate will be 5% for companies that are referred by DIT.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: Ctrip can assist for a fee
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Ctrip can assist for a fee
fields.dit_advisor_tip: OC&C Strategy Consultants found in a recent survey of Chinese consumers' online shopping habits that almost 60% of survey respondents buy only from apparel brands they are familiar with. Grabbing the attention of Chinese tourists when visiting the UK is a good place to start to build that familiarity.

fields.name: Mercado Libre
fields.description: Mercado Libre is the top e-commerce retailer in Latin America, operating in 18 countries. They are among the 50 most visited sites in the world (8th most visited retail site in the world). They receive 4,000 searches per second, and have 24 million buyers and 8 million sellers.
fields.customer_support_hours: 7 days a week, 18 hours a day
fields.seller_support_hours: 7 days a week, 18 hours a day
fields.customer_demographics: Broad demographic coverage due to the wide range of categories sold. Male and female across all ages and social levels.
fields.marketing_merchandising: They offer special promotion dates (Cyber Monday, Black Friday, hot sales, Fashion week, Electronics week etc.), as well as email and Facebook marketing, TV, radio and internet ads, branding campaigns.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer
fields.local_bank_account_needed_notes: Mercado Libre transfers the money to the bank account where the seller is located.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: The T&Cs and contract will be in English.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: A Spanish speaker is needed to manage the account (for customer service, pre and post sale, questions, claims etc.)
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Mercado Libre plan to add Seller support in English eventually.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: MercadoShops is a feature on Mercado Libre that allows brands to set up their own personalised online store within the website. This is a good option to boost brand awareness, while creating a dedicated destination for your products on Mercado Libre.

fields.name: Amazon India
fields.description:
Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas. 
Unlike other countries, Amazon in India only operates a wholesale-only model.
fields.customer_demographics: Men and women of all ages
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost:

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
In order to sell on Amazon India, sellers must identify a third party service provider to represent them in India. This company will provide the legal and financial entity for Amazon to trade with.

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

fields.name: Royal Mail Tmall Store
fields.description:
Tmall is a B2C platform that has over 400 million registered members and receives over 100 million unique visitors per day. Tmall is part of the Alibaba Group.
Recently Tmall has developed a service that enables brands from outside China to sell on its e-marketplace. This is called Tmall Global.
The Royal Mail store on Tmall Global offers UK companies a route to sell to consumers in China that combines low entry cost, presence on the Royal Mail branded domain alongside other UK brands, and the guarantee of protection from exchange rate movement.
fields.customer_demographics: Tmall demand is marginally higher in females, and the dominant age group is 25-45.
fields.marketing_merchandising: A range of marketing services exists, and can be tailored to budgets and related requirements.
fields.commission_notes: Paid on UK RRP once VAT deducted
fields.ukti_terms: Set-up cost reduced from £2,500 to £1,500 to register 5 products on Tmall, translate product text & upload product imagery. Account service charges of £100/ month waived for first 6 months trading.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: An easy, low-cost and rapid way for sellers to establish a presence on an e-marketplace in China. A budget to create a social media presence on digital channels outside Tmall Global must be part of the export plan.

fields.name: Kaola
fields.description: Kaola.com is a cross-border e-commerce platform selling Western brands, and forms part of the huge NetEase Corporation. With access to over 840 million subscribers of NetEase multiple services, Kaola.com offers an opportunity for UK brands to showcase their products across a huge number of online forums, portals and marketing channels. Kaola offers 2 business models of wholesale buying and an e-marketplace for sellers.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week; also through App
fields.seller_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week; also through App
fields.customer_demographics: The main products demanded by Kaola shoppers are: 1) Baby formula and baby products; 2) Packaged foods and nutrition products; 3) Cosmetics; 4) Household and personal care products; 5) Apparel and accessories; 6) Small consumer electronic products.
fields.marketing_merchandising: If brands offer exclusivity to Kaola, then Kaola will help them with marketing. It is essential to drive brand awareness in China for success in the market, so non-exclusive brands will need to set aside a budget for marketing and brand building.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Third Party Store management company to arrange
fields.ukti_terms: The first year's annual fee of USD$1000 is waived for DIT companies.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.dit_advisor_tip: When considering China as a market, you must register your trademark and set aside about 20% of projected turnover to a very well-targeted marketing campaign. To run the store successfully on Kaola, you will need the services of a third party to handle translations, customer service, imagery, etc.

fields.name: THE ICONIC
fields.description:
THE ICONIC is one of four e-marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other three are Namshi (The Gulf Region), LaModa (Russia & the former CIS) and Zalora in South East Asia. All Global Fashion Groups e-marketplaces sell top international and local fashion brands in fashion and beauty. 
THE ICONIC is the leading online fashion retailer in Australia and New Zealand, with 90% brand awareness among its core target audience. THE ICONIC launches over 200 new products each day and offers a wide range of delivery options to suit the needs of its community.
fields.customer_demographics: The customer gender split is 75% female and 25% male, of which the young professional female makes up the core consumer type. 50% of female customers also shop for male products as gifts.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
A range of marketing and communications products are available; shop in shop or branded landing page, on-site marketing banners, mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, in-house magazine, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

THE ICONIC can provide a tailored package depending on the marketing agreement with the brand.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell on THE ICONIC, brands will require a good level of international brand awareness, technical capability to integrate with the platform, and proven overseas fulfilment capability.

fields.name: Rakuten
fields.description: Rakuten is the fourth largest e-marketplace in the world, and is the leading platform in Japan. The consumer experience is similar to a "shopping mall" environment, and sellers can develop their own brand presence inside the marketplace using four different levels of plan. Rakuten has recently launched a new service to enable UK companies to sell directly to Japanese consumers.
fields.customer_demographics: 91.3% of Japanese internet users buy on Rakuten. Rakuen is used by men and women of all ages.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
There are four levels of store presentation that a seller can buy:

- Beginners Plan (19,500 Japanese Yen)

- Lite Plan (39,800 Japanese Yen)

- Standard Plan (50,000 Japanese Yen)

- Mega-Shop Plan (100,000 Japanese Yen)

Sellers can also buy performance marketing packages for search and/or banner advertising.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers will require a company to provide the legal and financial entity in Japan to trade on Rakuten. Example service providers are Brangista, Café 24, EC Robo, I-Order and TransCosmos. Sellers must arrange to receive payment in Yen and convert to Sterling, or ask the Service Provider to convert Yen to Sterling.

fields.name: Privalia
fields.description:
Privalia is a flash sales platform for fashion brands and retailers. It organises short, single-brand campaigns lasting between 3 and 5 days to which registered members are invited to shop via an email message and mobile alerts.

Sellers have an easy and profitable way of selling the remaining items in their inventory and customers obtain brand-name products at significantly lower prices than what they would find in stores.
fields.customer_demographics: Privalia in Spain has 8.5 million registered users and Privalia in Italy has 7.6 million registered users.70% of them are women between 30 and 45 years old. 60% are of medium to medium-high social profile and earn between 1200-2500€ a month. One in three users has children and buys for the whole family. This applies to both Spain and Italy.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Best price & discount products participate in high-profiile curated category events that Privalia manage.

Sellers can also organize specific branded events if the goods they offer can generate €15,000 sales across 2 days of activiy.
fields.ukti_terms: Reduced commission level. For brands, commission is reduced from 13% to 11%. For retailers, commission is reduced form 15% to 13%.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers must have a minimum of 300 Stock Keeping Units (SKUs) capability to deliver to Spain in 5 business days and Italian and Spanish language customer service to communicate with consumers.

fields.name: British Pavilion on 1688.com
fields.description:
Part of the Alibaba Group, 1688.com is the largest online B2B e-commerce marketplace in China, with over 120 million registered business users and a transaction value of approximately RMB 250 billion. 
1688.com is a seller marketplace using a local wholesale model, with stock held in warehouses in China. The British Food & Drink Pavilion is a platform on 1688.com, established to sell the best of British Food & Drink to the most reputable distributors across China. The British food and beverage store is run by LNP China and Global Food & Drink Brands, and is called 'The British Pavilion'.
fields.customer_demographics:
Buyers are all wholesale distributors / retailers. Located mainly in Beijing, Shanghai, Qingdao, Dalian, Chongqing, Guangzhou. The buyers have included mid-sized supermarket chains and owners of reputable online e-commerce stores in China.

Chinese distributors purchasing imported products from 1688.com will be targeting the rising middle class in China. British brands are attractive as they satisfy the customer requirements for quality, heritage, health and innovation.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brand awareness and brand building are essential parts of a successful strategy in China. An initial spend of 20% of projected annual turnover is considered a normal requirment.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: The British Pavilion will deal with logistics starting from a UK consolidation point & offering brand owners single pallet delivery options; stock is then held in China ready for sale
fields.ukti_terms: This is a wholesale model and prices are negotiated directly with LNP. The British Pavilion carries GREAT branding.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: This will be done by LNP China
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: This will be done by LNP China
fields.dit_advisor_tip: All products need to be fully compliant with Chinese food regulations. The British Pavilion charges upfront fees for import research reports, pricing, product registrations, translation and Chinese labelling. Payment terms are 30 days after sale in China.

fields.name: Jack Russell Emporium on JD.com
fields.description: JD.com is the second largest B2C e-commerce site in China, with 188 million active users. Jack Russell Emporium provides a one-stop, total solution to access the Chinese market from the UK on the JD Worldwide platform. Jack Russell Emporium offers a carefully curated selection of British premium and high street brands to the aspirational Chinese customer. Categories offered are Fashion, Health & Beauty and Homeware.
fields.customer_demographics: Aspirational middle class shoppers. 70% male with an average age of 38, 30% female with an average age of 37. In total, 69% of customers are from tier 1 and tier 2 cities, 23% from tier 3 cities and 8% spread across tiers 4 and 5.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Marketing through targeted Social Media and In-Channel promotion;
Promotional visibility on platform of 30M visits per day
Vendor brands feature in emporium marketing
Production house for creating campaigns
JRE own Chinese UK-based staff to refine brand message
Access to over 50,000 key opinion leaders including celebrities (TV/film), fashion magazines (Elle), bloggers (1m+ followers) and access to Chinese national newspapers.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK seller deliver to UK hub JRE take care of the rest
fields.ukti_terms: This is a cross border sales model where brands agree a wholesale price with the JRE London team.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: JRE UK headquarter will handle the matter in English
fields.translation_product_content_notes: JRE UK headquarter will handle the matter in English
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: JRE partner will handle the matter locally
fields.registration_fees_notes: By Negotiation with JRE London Team
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Aspirational middle class shoppers. 70% male with an average age of 38, 30% female with an average age of 37. In total, 69% of customers are from biggest 40% of cities, 23% from middle-sized cities and 8% spread across the 40% of smallest cities.

fields.name: SF Best
fields.description:
Launched in 2012, SF Commerce covers more than 60 first-tier, second-tier and third-tier cities in China, serving customers from online (SF Best) and offline community stores (SF Home and Heike). SF Best is the second largest Chinese e-commerce company focusing on food and drink. 
SF Best are looking to expand the number of UK food and drink brands they buy to offer to their 50 million registered users. The e-marketplace will buy the products, and this therefore requires individual commercial negotiations between brands and the SF Best buying teams. Categories include Seafood and Frozen Products, Snacks, Confectionary, Biscuits and Cereals.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week; also through App
fields.customer_demographics: Middle class, upper middle class and upper class households.
fields.marketing_merchandising: SF Best is more inclined to work with brands or agents who are willing to provide a marketing budget. Additional spending on marketing is voluntary, but effort on this will help to promote the brand and build its image in the long term.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: SF Best team in China will ask for basic information and graphics from UK suppliers
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Bulk delivery to nominated carrier with marketplace fulfilling to customer
fields.ukti_terms: None currently available as this is a wholesale model.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Carried out by SF Best at their cost
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Carried out by SF Best at their cost
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Brand awareness in China is a key to success in the market, and brands should set aside a reasonable budget to increase brand awareness amongst consumers. Trademark registration should be carried out as soon as possible.

fields.name: Amazon Italy
fields.description: Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas.
fields.customer_demographics: Men and women of all ages
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost:

Sponsored products: keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.

Amazon marketing services vary for each country.
fields.commission_notes: Paid per product sold & varies per category
fields.ukti_terms:
No current terms.

.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
By using Amazon's easy to use functionality, sellers can use their UK account to list products in Italy and three other European countries (France, Germany & Spain).

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.
